define({"topics" : [{"title":"Extending an XML catalog file","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can update either the main DITA-OT XML catalog or the XML catalog that is used by the PDF plug-in. This     enables the DITA-OT to support new specializations and document-type shells.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-xmlcatalog.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-xmlcatalog",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-xmlcatalog-d50e1660","topics":[]},{"title":"Adding a new target to the Ant build process","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">As of DITA-OT 3.0, the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ant.import</code> extension point can be used to make new targets     available to the Ant processing pipeline. This can be done as part of creating a new transformation, extending     pre-processing, or simply to make new Ant targets available to other plug-ins.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-anttarget.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-anttarget",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-anttarget-d50e1681","topics":[]},{"title":"Adding an Ant target to the pre-processing pipeline","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can add an Ant target to the pre-processing pipeline. This enables you to insert additional processing     before or after the pre-processing chain or a specific step in the pre-processing operation.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-antpreprocess.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-antpreprocess",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-antpreprocess-d50e1705","topics":[]},{"title":"Adding a new transformation type","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Plug-ins can add an entirely new transformation type. The new transformation type can be very simple,     such as an XHTML build that creates an additional control file; it also can be very complex, adding any number of     new processing steps.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-newtranstype.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-newtranstype",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-newtranstype-d50e1726","topics":[]},{"title":"Overriding an XSLT-processing step","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can override specific XSLT-processing steps in both the pre-processing pipeline and certain DITA-OT     transformations.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-overridestyle.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-overridestyle",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-overridestyle-d50e1747","topics":[]},{"title":"Referencing files from other plug-ins","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Starting with DITA-OT 1.5.4, you can use the <span class=\"ph filepath\">plugin:<var class=\"keyword varname\">plugin-id</var></span> URI extension and the <span class=\"ph filepath\">${dita.plugin.<var class=\"keyword varname\">plugin-id</var>.dir}</span> Ant variable to reference the     base path of another installed DITA-OT plug-in.</p>","href":"topics\/using-plugin-URI-extension.html","attributes": {"data-id":"using-plugin-URI-extension",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"using-plugin-URI-extension-d50e1768","topics":[]},{"title":"Adding parameters to existing XSLT steps","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can pass parameters from the Ant build to existing XSLT steps in both the pre-processing pipeline and     certain DITA-OT transformations. This can be useful if you want to make the parameters available as global       <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlelement\">&lt;xsl:param&gt;</code> values within XSLT overrides.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-xsltparams.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-xsltparams",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-xsltparams-d50e1800","topics":[]},{"title":"Adding a Java library to the DITA-OT <span class=\"keyword parmname\">classpath</span> parameter","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">dita.conductor.lib.import</code> extension point to add an additional Java     library to the DITA-OT <span class=\"keyword parmname\">classpath</span> parameter.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-javalib.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-javalib",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-javalib-d50e1824","topics":[]},{"title":"Adding new diagnostic messages","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">dita.xsl.messages</code> extension point to add plug-in-specific messages to the     diagnostic messages that are generated by the DITA-OT. These messages then can be used by any XSLT     override.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-messages.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-messages",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-messages-d50e1854","topics":[]},{"title":"Creating a new plug-in extension point","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If your plug-in needs to define its own extension point in an XML file, add the string       \"<code class=\"ph codeph\">_template</code>\" to the filename before the file suffix. When the plug-in is installed, this file will     be processed like the built-in DITA-OT templates.</p>","href":"topics\/plugin-newextensions.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-newextensions",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-newextensions-d50e1878","topics":[]}]});